Reports are the formated output of business data in d365 usally.(Invoices,Purchase orders,Ledger statements,Customer aging,Trial balance,Custom operational reports)
In Finops we use the most SSRS(SQL server Reporting services) reports .They run inside the application and can be export into the pdfs,mails,Excel etc..
The Architecture workflow of Reports (How it works)

Menu item / Print action
        ↓
Controller Class
        ↓
Contract (parameters)
        ↓
DP class (fetch data)
        ↓
Temp tables populated
        ↓
SSRS Design (.rdl)
        ↓
Rendered as PDF/Excel/Print

there are three types of reports 
1. Document Reports (Transaction Reports) 
2. Analytical Reports (Tabular Reports)
3.PowerBI / Embbeded Reports --( not SSRS ) 
--------------------------------------------------
 1. Data Contract Class :-

the data contract class holds the parameters like Date from / to
                                                  customer
                                                  status
2. Controller class :-
the controller class helps in control  Dailog and execution

3. Data Provider Class :-
fetches the data and fills temp tables.

4. TempTables :-
   table with datatye 

5. SSRS (RPL) :-
   visual layout of the report (Headers,layout,tables,groups)

--------------------------------------------------------------

How to create a Report (Step by Step)

--> Create Temp Table
--> Create Data Contract Class for parameters
--> Create Dp Class 
--> create SSRS Reports 
    1. To create Reports >> Project >> right click >> add >> new item >> Report
--> Create Controller
--> Create Menu item 
 



